23/02/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu announced on Wednesday (22 February) that draft legal changes are being prepared that would restrict former collaborators of the communist-era security services Securitate from serving in public office. He stressed that any individuals in public administration who are found to have collaborated with Securitate would immediately lose their posts. (Nine o'clock - 23/02/06)
